{"from":"manager","to":"eng-1-2","body":"TASK 11: Implement src/opening_book.py + tests/test_opening_book.py\n\nPull main first: git merge main\n\nCreate src/opening_book.py:\n\nimport random\nfrom src.board import Board\nfrom src.constants import encode_move, QUIET, DOUBLE_PAWN, CAPTURE, CASTLE_KING, CASTLE_QUEEN\n\nBOOK: dict[str, list[int]] = {\n    # Map position FEN (without move counters) -> list of encoded moves\n    # Use board.get_position_fen() as the key\n}\n\ndef get_book_move(board: Board) -> int | None:\n    key = board.get_position_fen()\n    moves = BOOK.get(key)\n    if moves:\n        return random.choice(moves)\n    return None\n\nBuild the BOOK dict with 20-30 positions covering common openings:\n- Starting position: e4 (encode_move(12, 28, DOUBLE_PAWN)), d4 (encode_move(11, 27, DOUBLE_PAWN)), Nf3, c4\n- After 1.e4: e5, c5 (Sicilian), e6 (French), c6 (Caro-Kann)\n- After 1.d4: d5, Nf6 (Indian)\n- Italian Game line: 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4\n- Sicilian line: 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3\n- Queen's Gambit: 1.d4 d5 2.c4\n\nTo build each position FEN key: create Board(), make the moves to reach that position, then call get_position_fen(). Hard-code the resulting string as the dict key.\n\nTests (tests/test_opening_book.py):\n- test_starting_position_has_book_move: get_book_move(Board()) returns a move (not None)\n- test_unknown_position_returns_none: random position returns None\n- test_book_move_is_legal: returned move is in generate_legal_moves(board)\n- test_e4_response: after 1.e4, book has a response\n- test_d4_response: after 1.d4, book has a response\n- test_multiple_openings: book covers both e4 and d4 lines\n\nRun: python -m pytest tests/test_opening_book.py -v","msg_type":"assign","timestamp":1773174601}